> I have a '72 Kombi in *running* condition. I left it for two or three weeks
> over winter (no extreme cold, just wetness so far as the weather went) and
> now it will not move. The engine will run and sounds and works fine, but it
> is as if there are imaginary blocks behind the drive wheels. I gave it some
> gas in reverse and the right rear went "clunk" and I could feel the
> resistance go away from that wheel. But, no matter what i try the left rear
> is locked. Is it ceased? Could it be transmission or brake related?
> 
> Thanks,
> - Ian
